-- Seiyu says Wal-Mart will not pull out of Japan
-- 
-- Tue Aug 14, 2007 3:31am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/14/us-seiyu-results-exit-idUSTFA00285120070814

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Wal-Mart Stores Inc. has no plans to pull out of Japan despite continued losses at its Japanese unit, Seiyu Ltd., Seiyu Chief Executive Ed Kolodzieski told reporters on Tuesday. 

 Wal-Mart has a 53.6 percent stake in Seiyu, which earlier on  Tuesday said it now expects to post its sixth straight annual loss in 2007 due to sluggish sales.